  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Current validator implementations put a lot of trust in constructing the attestation data object on the beacon node side, mostly the validator checks the attestation data is not slashable. \r\n\r\nA problem can occur if the attestation data includes a target epoch well into the future. If the validator signs it, from that point on, most slashing protection mechanism will prevent that validator from signing any attestation until that far into the future epoch is reached. \r\nThat can cause major loses and potential inactivity slashing.\r\n\r\nIt might be a good idea to add some reference to this in the honest validator guide (thanks for the suggestion @dankrad ) ",
